 and export customers\u2019 specifications. Ensuring pack-house standard including temperature (cold rooms) regulations are met. Generating water allocation in line with crop-water requirements and usage reports. Management of Contractor performance (SLA/SOW) through monthly evaluations of services rendered. Compiling and adhering to fruit budgets by generating cost, cash flow and forecast reports together with weekly sales recons Compiling weekly marketing and sales reports and monthly forecast reports. Monitoring and regularly updating business risk profile and ensure compliance. Managing and compiling Eurep Gap, SUS Farms and MARSH Audit standards. Compiling and updating a 3 (three) year alien plant control program. Minimum Requirements Diploma in Agriculture (Plant Production) or equivalent. Minimum 5 years\u2019 experience mostly in banana production. 5 years Agronomy, Agricultural Management and Water and Irrigation Management experience. 5 years Fruits Production and Pack-house Management experience. 3 years Soil Science experience. Computer proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Outlook) Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
